arch_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to delight, to rejoice","examples":[{"text":"زَعَمَ الْفَرَزْدَقُ أَنْ سَيَقْتَلُ مَرْبَعًا\n أَبْشِرْ بِطُولِ سَلَامَةٍ يَا مَرْبَعُ"},{"text":"[…]وَأَبْشِرُوا بِالْجَنَّةِ الَّتِي كُنْتُمْ تُوعَدُونَ","english":"\" […] but receive good tidings of Paradise, which you were promised.\""}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make happy, to cause to delight"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to blossom, to become verdant (of the earth)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2591","headword_ar":"ابشر","root":"b$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, first sentence, in two places. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ab$r AlA^amoru wajohahu","text_ar":"ابشر الاَمْرُ وَجْهَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The affair made his countenance beautiful and bright:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K we read,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abo$ara AlA^amora Has~anahu wa naD~arahu","text_ar":"اَبْشَرَ الاَمْرَ حَسَّنَهُ وَ نَضَّرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is a mistake. (TA.) Agreeably with this explanation, AA renders a reading in the Kur [xlii. 22],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika A@l~a*iY","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ ا@لَّذِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yubo$iru A@ll~`hu EibaAdahu","text_ar":"يُبْشِرُ ا@للّٰهُ عِبَادَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is it with which God will make beautiful and bright"},{"kind":"text","text":"the face of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his servants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the L. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also 2. ―         -b4-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abo$arati Aln~aAqapu","text_ar":"اَبْشَرَتِ النَّاقَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-camel conceived,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became pregnant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) as though she rejoiced [her owner] by announcing her conception. (TA. [See 2, last sentence.]) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abo$arati","text_ar":"اَبْشَرَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The earth put forth its herbage appearing upon its surface."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)       -A2-  See also 1, latter part, in four places."}],"source_refs":["K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}